Create Blazor Server interactive pages for the VetClinic patient management feature in /tmp/sv-507ad7f14691479db30a32d04e590a64/VetClinic/Components/Pages/Patients/

The project uses .NET (net11.0), Blazor Web App with Interactive Server rendering, EF Core with SQLite, ASP.NET Core Identity. Services are already created.

Available service (injected as `PatientService`):
```csharp
public class PatientService(ApplicationDbContext db)
{
    public async Task<List<Owner>> GetOwnersAsync(string? search = null)
    public async Task<Owner?> GetOwnerAsync(int id)
    public async Task<Owner> SaveOwnerAsync(Owner owner)
    public async Task<Pet?> GetPetAsync(int id) // includes Owner, TreatmentNotes
    public async Task<List<Pet>> GetAllPetsAsync()
    public async Task<Pet> SavePetAsync(Pet pet)
    public async Task<TreatmentNote> AddTreatmentNoteAsync(TreatmentNote note)
    public async Task<TreatmentNote> UpdateTreatmentNoteAsync(TreatmentNote note)
    public async Task DeleteTreatmentNoteAsync(int id)
}
```

Models:
```csharp
public class Owner { int Id; string FirstName; string LastName; string? Phone; string? Email; string FullName; List<Pet> Pets; }
public class Pet { int Id; string Name; string Species; string? Breed; DateOnly? DateOfBirth; double? WeightKg; string? Microchip; int OwnerId; Owner Owner; List<TreatmentNote> TreatmentNotes; List<Appointment> Appointments; }
public class TreatmentNote { int Id; int PetId; Pet Pet; DateTime Date; string Title; string Description; string? Veterinarian; }
```

Create these pages (all must have `@attribute [Authorize]` and `@rendermode InteractiveServer`):

1. **Patients.razor** (`@page "/patients"`) - List all owners and their pets. Include a search bar that filters in real-time. Show owner name, phone, and number of pets. Each row has Edit/View buttons. Include "Register New Owner" button that navigates to the form.

2. **OwnerForm.razor** (`@page "/patients/owner/new"` and `@page "/patients/owner/{Id:int}"`) - Form to create/edit an owner. Fields: FirstName, LastName, Phone, Email. Uses EditForm with validation. On save, navigate back to patients list. Shows list of owner's pets if editing existing owner with links to each pet.

3. **PetForm.razor** (`@page "/patients/pet/new/{OwnerId:int}"` and `@page "/patients/pet/{Id:int}"`) - Form to create/edit a pet. Fields: Name, Species (dropdown: Dog, Cat, Bird, Rabbit, Reptile, Other), Breed, DateOfBirth, WeightKg, Microchip. Owner is pre-selected or shown. On save, navigate to pet detail page.

4. **PetDetail.razor** (`@page "/patients/pet/{Id:int}/detail"`) - Shows pet info, owner info, and full medical history (treatment notes in reverse chronological order). Each treatment note shows Date, Title, Description, Veterinarian. Has "Add Treatment Note" button that shows an inline form. Treatment notes can be edited inline or deleted with confirmation.

Use Bootstrap CSS classes (already included). Use `NavigationManager` for navigation. All pages in namespace that matches directory.

Use `@using VetClinic.Data.Models` and `@using VetClinic.Services` and `@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization` and `@inject PatientService PatientService` and `@inject NavigationManager Navigation`.

Create Blazor Server interactive pages for the VetClinic appointment scheduling feature in /tmp/sv-507ad7f14691479db30a32d04e590a64/VetClinic/Components/Pages/Appointments/

The project uses .NET (net11.0), Blazor Web App with Interactive Server rendering, EF Core with SQLite.

Available service (injected as `AppointmentService`):
```csharp
public class AppointmentService(ApplicationDbContext db)
{
    public async Task<List<Appointment>> GetAppointmentsAsync(DateTime? from = null, DateTime? to = null)
    public async Task<Appointment?> GetAppointmentAsync(int id)
    public async Task<Appointment> SaveAppointmentAsync(Appointment appointment)
    public async Task CancelAppointmentAsync(int id)
    public async Task<List<Appointment>> GetAvailabilitySlotsAsync(DateTime date)
    public async Task<bool> IsSlotAvailableAsync(DateTime start, DateTime end, int? excludeId = null)
}
```

Also available: `PatientService` with `GetAllPetsAsync()` to get list of pets for selection.

Models:
```csharp
public enum AppointmentStatus { Scheduled, Completed, Cancelled }
public class Appointment { int Id; int PetId; Pet Pet; DateTime StartTime; DateTime EndTime; string Reason; string? Veterinarian; AppointmentStatus Status; string? Notes; }
public class Pet { int Id; string Name; string Species; Owner Owner; }
public class Owner { string FullName; }
```

Create these pages (all must have `@attribute [Authorize]` and `@rendermode InteractiveServer`):

1. **Appointments.razor** (`@page "/appointments"`) - Shows a weekly calendar view. User can navigate between weeks with Previous/Next buttons. Shows current week by default. Display appointments as colored blocks (green=Scheduled, gray=Completed, red=Cancelled). Each day column shows time slots from 8:00 to 18:00. Clicking on a time slot opens the appointment form. Clicking on existing appointment shows details with options to reschedule or cancel. Include a "New Appointment" button. Show real-time availability - occupied slots are highlighted.

2. **AppointmentForm.razor** (`@page "/appointments/new"` and `@page "/appointments/{Id:int}"`) - Form to create/edit (reschedule) appointments. Fields: Pet (searchable dropdown showing "PetName - OwnerName"), Date picker, Start Time (dropdown in 30-min intervals from 8:00-17:30), Duration (30min, 60min, 90min dropdown), Reason, Veterinarian (text input), Notes. Before saving, check availability and show warning if slot is taken. On save, navigate back to appointments calendar. If editing, pre-populate all fields.

Use `@using VetClinic.Data.Models`, `@using VetClinic.Services`, `@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization`, `@inject AppointmentService AppointmentService`, `@inject PatientService PatientService`, `@inject NavigationManager Navigation`.

Use Bootstrap CSS classes. The calendar should use a simple table-based layout with Bootstrap styling.

Create Blazor Server interactive pages for the VetClinic billing feature in /tmp/sv-507ad7f14691479db30a32d04e590a64/VetClinic/Components/Pages/Billing/

The project uses .NET (net11.0), Blazor Web App with Interactive Server rendering, EF Core with SQLite.

Available service (injected as `BillingService`):
